<HL>
   CAE Unit Gets Simulator Job
</HL>
<DATE>
05/23/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C9
</SO>
<CO>
   T.CAE AWAL
</CO>
<LP>
   TORONTO -- CAE Industries Ltd. said its CAE Electronics
Ltd. unit was awarded a 23.5 million Canadian dollar (US$20
million) contract by America West Airlines, of Phoenix,
Ariz., to design and make flight simulators.
   The simulators will be for de Havilland Dash 8 and Boeing
737-300/400 aircraft. The project, which includes simulators,
visual systems and facilities, is scheduled for 1992. CAE is
a manufacturer of military and commercial flight simulators
and aviation equipment.
</LP>
