   Business Brief -- ABB Group:
   Asea Brown Unit to Sell
   C-E Minerals to Imetal S.A.
</HL>
<DATE>
05/23/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B5
</SO>
<CO>
   F.IME S.ABB MDEST ASEAY
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
HEAVY CONSTRUCTION; INDUSTRIAL AND COMMERCIAL (CON)
</IN>
<LP>
   Asea Brown Boveri Inc. said in Stamford, Conn., that it
agreed to sell its C-E Minerals unit to Imetal S.A. for about
$150 million.
   Asea Brown Boveri, the U.S. unit of ABB Group, Zurich,
Switzerland, said it seeks to focus on its core businesses,
including products and services to the power, automation,
environmental control, transit and other markets.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   C-E Minerals, King of Prussia, Pa., is a supplier of
alumina silica calcines and fused silica used in the
refractory, investment casting and semiconductor industries.
Imetal, Paris, is a building materials, industrial minerals,
metal fabricating and international trading concern.
   Separately, Asea Brown Boveri won a $450 million contract
to build an electric power station at Bahrain's aluminum
smelter, officials of the state-controlled Aluminium Bahrain
(Alba) said.
   The power plant project station forms part of Alba's $1.4
billion plan to expand output at the island's aluminum
smelter to about 460,000 metric tons a year from around
210,000.
