<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C9
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP FNM UN UL GWF
</CO>
<IN>
MORTGAGES, MORTGAGE BANKERS, MORTGAGE-BACKED SECURITIES (MOR)
BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)
BANKS (BNK)
</IN>
<LP>
   The following were among yesterday's offerings and
pricings in U.S. and non-U.S. capital markets, with terms and
syndicate manager, as compiled by Dow Jones Capital Markets
Report:
                                                                                                       

                        CORPORATES
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   Great Western Bank -- $130 million of 10 1/2% subordinated
notes, due May 30, 2000, priced at 99.625 to yield 10.562%.
The notes are noncallable for 8 3/4 years and are then
callable at par for the last 15 months. Rated Baa-1 by
Moody's and single-A-minus by S&amp;P, the issue will be sold
through underwriters led by Merrill Lynch Capital Markets.
                                                                                                       

                        MUNICIPALS
                                                                                                       

   Connecticut -- $250 million special tax general obligation
transportation infrastructure bonds, due June 1, 1992-2004,
2007 and 2010, tentatively priced by a Bear Stearns &amp; Co.
group to yield from 6.10% in 1992 to 7.23% in 2007. Current
interest serial bonds are priced to yield from 6.10% in 1992
to 7.10% in 2004. There are $51.91 million of 7 7/8% term
bonds priced at 99 to yield 7.23% in 2007. There are $63.81
million of 7 1/8% term bonds priced at par in 2010. The bonds
are rated single-A-1 by Moody's and double-A-minus by S&amp;P.
   Louisiana Offshore Terminal Authority -- $102.2 million of
deep water port refunding revenue bonds, Loop Inc. Project,
due Sept. 1, 1993-2003, and 2010, tentatively priced by a
First Boston Corp. group to yield from 6.60% in 1993 to 7.63%
in 2010. Current interest serial bonds are priced at par to
yield from 6.60% in 1993 to 7.40% in 2003. There are $49.27
million of 7 5/8% term bonds priced at par in 2010. The bonds
are rated single-A-3 by Moody's and single-A by S&amp;P.
   Passaic Valley Sewerage Commissioners, New Jersey -- $86.5
million sewer system revenue bonds, Series C, due Dec. 1,
1991-2006, 2010 and 2020, apparently won by a First Boston
Corp. group. The bonds, AMBAC-insured and rated triple-A by
both Moody's and S&amp;P, priced to yield from 6% 1991 to 7.26%
in 2020. Current interest serial bonds are priced to yield
from 6% in 1991 to 7.15% in 2005 and 2006. There are $11.9
million of 7.10% term bonds priced at 98 5/8 to yield 7.23%
in 2010. There are $49.6 million of 7.10% term bonds priced
at 98 to yield 7.26% in 2020.
   Harris County Health Facility Authority, Texas -- $65
million special facility revenue bonds, Texas Medical Center
Project, due May 15, 1996-2000, 2005 and 2020, tentatively
priced by a First Boston Corp. group to yield from 6.6% in
1996 to 7.42% in 2020. Current interest serial bonds are
priced to yield from 6.6% in 1996 to 7% in 2000. There are $8
million of 7 1/4% term bonds priced at 99 1/2 to yield 7.31%
in 2005. There are $51 million of 7 3/8% term bonds priced at
99 1/2 to yield 7.42% in 2020. The bonds are MBIA-insured and
rated triple-A by both Moody's and S&amp;P.
   Suffolk County, N.Y. -- $56.42 million public improvement
revenue bonds, Series B, portion of a $80.07 million revenue
bond and 12-month capital notes issue was won by a Citibank
Securities Markets Inc. group. The bonds, due April 1 and May
1, 1991-2020, were priced for reoffering to yield from 6.10%
