<LP>
   C-TEC Corp. said it raised its stake in Mercom Inc. to
19.9% from 11.68% of the common stock outstanding.
   In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission,
C-TEC said it holds 475,665 shares, including 152,920 shares
bought from May 3 to May 8 for $10.46 to $11.29 each.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   A spokesman for C-TEC, Wilkes-Barre, Pa., declined to
comment on whether discussions have begun with Bloomfield
Hills, Mich.-based Mercom management and whether C-TEC plans
to increase its stake. Mercom declined to comment.
   In its previous filing, C-TEC said it planned to seek
discussions with Mercom's management regarding its business
and policies.
