<LP>
   DENVER -- Amoco Corp. said it made a "significant" natural
gas discovery in the Ouachita Thrust area of the Arkoma Basin
in southeastern Oklahoma.
   The well, the Amoco Retherford No. 1A, tested at a natural
flow rate of 49.3 million cubic feet of natural gas a day,
Amoco said.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company said perforations in the Pennsylvanian Spiro
sandstone were between 12,142 and 12,170 feet. Amoco is the
operator, with about a 42% working interest, and Exxon Corp.
holds the remaining 58% working interest.
